nodes.title: What settings should I change?
widgets_values:
1. Positive Prompt (Green box): This is the text that guides your image. The more detailed, the better. Think about subject, scene, style, color, etc. when composing a prompt.

2. Negative Prompt (Red box): These are things you DON'T want to include in your images. Negative prompts won't guarantee that these things will be removed, but it still helps to use them.

3. ControlNet Strength: How much the ControlNet model influences the output image.

4. + 5. ControlNet Start Percent and End Percent:
Decide WHEN the ControlNet model starts and stops influencing the output image during the generation process. For example, if START is 0 and END is 1, that means that ControlNet will be applied at EACH STEP of the image generating process.

6. Steps: Keep this low (~10) while testing things out so that you can iterate more quickly. Increase it to ~20 when you're ready for your final video.

7. CFG (Classifier Free Guidance): This number (sort of) controls how closely your image matches your prompt. Higher numbers (8-20) are more "controlled", but are often oversaturated and have high contrast. Lower numbers (2-7) are more "free associating". Try a range of numbers! For this workshop, we recommend somewhere between 3-8 

8. Global Seed: Set action to "randomize" if you want to try different seeds. Set it to "fixed" if you want to stick with the same seed.

nodes.title: Metadata Extractor
widgets_values:
KSU AI Animation Workshop
Aviva Avnisan and Doug Rosman

Metadata Extractor

Extract the prompts and settings from an image you generated.

############

Instructions:

1. Download one of your images from the file RunDiffusion File Explorer

2. Drag and drop your downloaded image onto the "Load image with metadata" node

3. Click the play button in the top right corner of the blue Metadata Extractor window

4. Copy and paste any of the extracted metadata that you would like to use to generate your video

nodes.title: Start Here!
widgets_values:
KSU AI Animation Workshop
Aviva Avnisan and Doug Rosman

Workflow 2: Video2Video

Transform an input video into an animation

############

Instructions:

1. Set your group name in the 'Group Name' node
2. In the "Load Video" Node, click "choose video to upload" and select your video.
3. Get the metadata from one of the images you generated using the Metadata Extractor to the left, and use those settings as desired in this workflow
4. Tweak parameters in the purple nodes; click "Queue Prompt" to generate a video. Do this a few times until you've found something you like.
5. When you're ready, increase Steps to a higher number (~20) and disable the "bypass" feature in Video Upscaling to generate a higher quality video.
